Meet <b>Duck Man</b>, our Millsberry Citizen of the Week!<br><br>Duck has lived at <a href='/home/?user=duck_man'>17695 Post Road</a>, Metro Park since August, 2006. <br><br>Just by looking at his trophy collection, you can clearly see that he's a well-rounded guy. Mastering both Sports and Solver while still managing to help out in his community makes Duck a true Renaissance man. He's achieved a level of expertise in the Home Run Derby, Rope Race, Peabody Park Half Pipe, Sink the Three, and has also received a trophy for the Peabody Park Clean Up. Leonardo Da Vinci would be proud.  <br><br>Duck also has a Botany collection in his back yard that would make any gardening enthusiast swoon.  If you're in the area, you should drop by and ask him to show you all the lush botanicals he's growing. Don't worry about working up a sweat. He may invite you to take a dip in his pool while you're there.<br><br>You really don't want to miss Duck's yard sale. He has a couple of pretty rare items in it right now.  Among the hot pieces in his collection is his limited edition Sylvie hat.  It's not one-size-fits-all, so you should probably try it on before you make a purchase. All sales are final. <br><br>We'd like to congratulate Duck on being name our Citizen of the Week and to thank him for being such a good neighbor to all of us in Millsberry. Keep up the good work, Duck!<br><br><br><br></div>
